Alarm.Name: AL001
Alarm.Title: Overcurrent
Alarm.Result1: The drive output is short-circuit
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the wiring between the motor and the drive is correct and see if the wire is short-circuited. Eliminate short-circuit and avoid metal conductor being exposed.
Alarm.Result2: The motor wiring is in error.
Alarm.Solve2: Check if the wiring steps are correct when connecting the motor to the drive. Rewiring by following the wiring description from the user manual.
Alarm.Solve3: The temperature of the heat sink is abnormal. Send the drive back to the distributors or contact with Delta.
Alarm.Result4: The control parameter setting is in error.
Alarm.Solve4: Check if the setting value exceeds the default setting Setting back to the default setting and then gradually adjust the value.
Alarm.Solve5: Check if the command doing reasonable acceleration time. Less steep command used or filter applying to smooth command.

Alarm.Name: AL002
Alarm.Title: Overvoltage
Alarm.Result1: The input voltage of the main circuit is higher than the rated allowable voltage.
Alarm.Solve1: Use the voltmeter to see if the input voltage of the main circuit is within the rated allowable voltage value. Apply to the correct power supply or serial voltage regulator.
Alarm.Solve2: Use the voltmeter to see if the power system matches the specification. Apply to the correct power supply or serial adaptor.
Alarm.Result3: The hardware of the servo drive is damaged.
Alarm.Solve3: Use the voltmeter to see if the input voltage of the main circuit is within the rated allowable voltage value but still shows the error. Send the drive back to the distributors or contact with Delta.

Alarm.Name: AL003
Alarm.Title: Undervoltage
Alarm.Result1: The input voltage of the main circuit is lower than the rated allowable voltage.
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the input voltage wiring of the main circuit is normal. Re-confirm the voltage wiring.
Alarm.Result2: No power supply for the main circuit.
Alarm.Solve2: Use the voltmeter to see if the voltage of the main circuit is normal. Check the power switch
Alarm.Solve3: Use the voltmeter to see if the power system matches the specification. Apply to the correct power supply or serial adaptor.

Alarm.Name: AL004
Alarm.Title: Motor Combination Error
Alarm.Result1: The encoder is abnormal
Alarm.Solve1: The encoder is abnormal.Change the motor
Alarm.Solve2: Check the encoder connector. Install the motor again.
Alarm.Solve3: Connect to the right motor. Change the motor

Alarm.Name: AL005
Alarm.Title: Regeneration Error
Alarm.Result1: Wrong selection of regenerative resistor or the external regenerative resistor is unconnected.
Alarm.Solve1: Check the connection of regenerative resistor. Reconnect the regenerative resistor or calculate the regenerative resistor value. If the alarm does not go off, please send the drive back to the distributor or contact with Delta.
Alarm.Result2: Parameter P1-53 is not set to zero when the regenerative resistor is not in use.
Alarm.Solve2: Check if parameter P1-53 of regenerative resister is set to zero. Set parameter P1-53 of regenerative resistor to zero when it is not applying.
Alarm.Solve3: Check the setting value of parameter P1-52 and P1-53. Correctly reset the value of P1-52 and P1-53.

Alarm.Name: AL006
Alarm.Title: Overload
Alarm.Result1: Over the rated loading of the drive and continuously excessive using
Alarm.Solve1: Set parameter P0-02 to 11 and see if the average torque [%] is over 100% all the time. Increase the motor capacity or reduce the load.
Alarm.Result2: The setting of the control system parameter is inappropriate.
Alarm.Solve2: 1. Adjust the gain value of the control circuit. 2. Slow down the acceleration / deceleration setting time.
Alarm.Result3: Wrong wiring of the motor and the encoder.
Alarm.Solve3: Check the wiring of U, V, W and the encoder. Correct wiring
Alarm.Result4: The encoder of the motor is defective.
Alarm.Solve4: Send the drive back to the distributors or contact with Delta.

Alarm.Name: AL007
Alarm.Title: Overspeed
Alarm.Result1: Unreasonable command
Alarm.Solve1: Use the scope to check if the signal of analog voltage is abnormal. Less steep command used or filter applying to smooth command.
Alarm.Solve2: Check if the setting of parameter P2-34 is too small (the condition of over-speed warning). Correctly set parameter P2-34 (the condition of over-speed warning).

Alarm.Name: AL008
Alarm.Title: Abnormal Pulse Command
Alarm.Result1: The pulse command frequency is higher than the rated input frequency.
Alarm.Solve1: Use the scope to check if the input frequency is over the rated input frequency. Correctly set the input pulse frequency.

Alarm.Name: AL009
Alarm.Title: Excessive Deviation of Position Command
Alarm.Result1: Parameter P2-35 is set too small
Alarm.Solve1: Check the setting value of parameter P2-35 (The warning condition of excessive position deviation) Increase the setting value of P2-35 (The warning condition of excessive position deviation)
Alarm.Result2: The setting of the gain value is too small.
Alarm.Solve2: Check if the setting value is appropriate. Correctly adjust the gain value
Alarm.Result3: The torque limit is too low.
Alarm.Solve3: Check the torque limit value Correctly adjust the torque limit value. Check the external load Reduce the external load or evaluate the motor capacity again
Alarm.Solve4: Check the external load. Reduce the external load or evaluate the motor capacity again

Alarm.Name: AL011
Alarm.Title: Encoder Error
Alarm.Result1: Wrong wiring of the encoder
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the wiring follows the suggested wiring of the user manual. Correct wiring
Alarm.Solve2: Check the drive connector of CN2 and encoder. Install the encoder again
Alarm.Solve3: Check if the connection between CN2 of the drive and the encoder of the servo motor is loose. Reconnect the wiring
Alarm.Solve4: Check if the motor is damaged. Change the motor

Alarm.Name: AL012
Alarm.Title: Adjustment Error
Alarm.Result1: The analog input contact is incorrectly set back to zero
Alarm.Solve1: Measure if the voltage of the analog input contact is the same as the ground voltage. Correctly ground the analog input contact
Alarm.Solve2: Reset the power supply. If the error still occurs after reset, send the drive back to the distributors or contact with Delta.

Alarm.Name: AL013
Alarm.Title: Emergency Stop
Alarm.Result1: Press the system emergency stop switch
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the TP emergency stop switch is enabled. Activate emergency stop
Alarm.Result2: Press the external emergency stop switch
Alarm.Solve2: Check the circuit emergency stop whether correct
Alarm.Solve3: Check the function of system DI1 whether abnormal
Alarm.Solve4: Please push Deadman switch at middle of position
Alarm.Solve5: Check the fence or safety device whether enabled
Alarm.Solve6: Check the temperature inside the electric control box is too high or the temperature sensor

Alarm.Name: AL014
Alarm.Title: Reverse Limit Error
Alarm.Result1: Reverse limit switch is activated.
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the limit switch is enabled. Enable the reverse limit switch
Alarm.Solve2: Check the control parameter and inertia ratio. Re-adjust the parameter or evaluate the motor capacity.

Alarm.Name: AL015
Alarm.Title: Forward Limit Error
Alarm.Result1: Forward limit switch is activated.
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the limit switch is enabled. Enable the forward limit switch
Alarm.Solve2: Check the control parameter and inertia ratio Re-adjust the parameter or evaluate the motor capacity.

Alarm.Name: AL016
Alarm.Title: IGBT Overheat
Alarm.Result1: Over the rated loading of the drive and continuously excessive using
Alarm.Solve1: Check if it is overloading or the motor current is too high. Increase the motor capacity or reduce the load.
Alarm.Solve2: Check the drive output wiring Correct wiring

Alarm.Name: AL017
Alarm.Title: Abnormal EEPROM
Alarm.Result1: It is in error when DSP accesses EEPROM.
Alarm.Solve1: Press the SHIFT Key on the panel and it shows EXGAB.X = 1, 2, 3 G＝group code of the parameter AB＝hexadecimal of the parameter. If it shows E320A, it means it is parameter P2-10; If it shows E3610, it means it is parameter P6-16. Please check the parameter.
Alarm.Solve2: Press the SHIFT Key on the panel and it shows E100X. The fault occurs in parameter reset. The setting of the drive is wrong. Please set the correct type of the drive.
Alarm.Solve3: Press the SHIFT Key on the panel and it shows E0001. The fault occurs when it is servo-on. Usually it is because the data in ROM is damaged or there is no data in ROM. Please send the drive back to the distributors or contact with Delta.

Alarm.Name: AL018
Alarm.Title: Abnormal Signal Output
Alarm.Result1: The encoder is in error and cause the abnormal signal output
Alarm.Solve1: Check the fault records (P4-00~P4-05). See if the alarm exists with the encoder error (AL011, AL024, AL025, AL026)
Alarm.Result2: The output pulse exceeds the hardware allowable range.
Alarm.Solve2: Check if the following conditions produce: P1-76 < Motor Speed

Alarm.Name: AL019
Alarm.Title: Serial Communication Error
Alarm.Result1: Improper setting of the communication parameter
Alarm.Solve1: Check the setting value of communication parameter. Correctly set the parameter value
Alarm.Solve2: Check the communication address. Correctly set the communication address
Alarm.Solve3: Check the accessing value. Correctly set the value

Alarm.Name: AL020
Alarm.Title: Serial Communication Time Out
Alarm.Result1: Improper setting of the time-out parameter
Alarm.Solve1: Check the parameter setting. Correctly set the value
Alarm.Result2: The drive hasn’t received the communication command for a long time.
Alarm.Solve2: Check if the communication cable is loose or broken. Correct wiring

Alarm.Name: AL022
Alarm.Title: Safety Stop
Alarm.Result1: Press the system Safety stop switch
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the TP Safety stop switch is enabled. Activate Safety stop
Alarm.Result2: Press the external Safety stop switch
Alarm.Solve2: Check the circuit Safety stop whether correct
Alarm.Solve3: Check the function of system DI1 whether abnormal
Alarm.Solve4: Please push Deadman switch at middle of position
Alarm.Solve5: Check the fence or safety device whether enableed
Alarm.Solve6: Check the temperature inside the electric control box is too high or the temperature sensor

Alarm.Name: AL023
Alarm.Title: Early warning for overload
Alarm.Result1: Early warning for overload
Alarm.Solve1: 1.Please refer to the corrective actions of AL006. 2.Please increase the setting value of parameter P1-56. Or set the value over 100 and deactivate the overload warning function.

Alarm.Name: AL024
Alarm.Title: Encoder initial magnetic field error
Alarm.Result1: The initial magnetic field of the encoder is in error(Signal U, V, W of the encoder magnetic field is in error.)
Alarm.Solve1: 1. Check if the servo is properly grounded. 2. Check if the encoder cable separates from the power supply or the high-current circuit to avoid the interference. 3. Check if the shielding cables are used in the wiring of the encoder.

Alarm.Name: AL025
Alarm.Title: The internal of the encoder is in error
Alarm.Result1: The internal of the encoder is in error.(The internal memory and the internal counter are in error)
Alarm.Solve1: 1. Check if the servo is properly grounded. 2. Check if the encoder cable separates from the power supply or the high-current circuit to avoid the interference. 3. Check if the shielding cables are used in the wiring of the encoder.

Alarm.Name: AL026
Alarm.Title: Unreliable internal data of the encoder
Alarm.Result1: The encoder is in error.(Errors occur in the internal data for three times continuously)
Alarm.Solve1: 1. Please connect the UVW connector (color green) to the heat sink of the servo drive. 2. Please check if the encoder cable separates from the power supply or the high-current circuit. 3. Please use shielding mesh. 4. If the situation is not improving, please send the drive back to the distributors or contact with Delta.

Alarm.Name: AL027
Alarm.Title: The internal of the Encoder is in error
Alarm.Result1: The internal reset of the encoder is in error.
Alarm.Solve1: 1. Please connect the UVW connector (color green) to the heat sink of the servo drive. 2. Please check if the encoder cable separates from the power supply or the high-current circuit. 3. Please use shielding mesh. 4. If the situation is not improving, please send the drive back to the distributors or contact with Delta.

Alarm.Name: AL028
Alarm.Title: Encoder voltage error or the internal of the encoder is in error
Alarm.Result1: Battery voltage is too high.
Alarm.Solve1: Please do the check according to the procedure Over voltage. When corrective actions are done, AL028 will be cleared automatically.
Alarm.Result2: The internal encoder is in error.
Alarm.Solve2: 1. If the situation is not improving, please send the drive back to the distributors or contact with Delta. 2. Please connect the UVW connector (color green) to the heat sink of the servo drive. 3. Please check if the encoder cable separates from the power supply or the high-current circuit. 4. Please use shielding mesh. If the situation is not improving, please send the drive back to the distributors or contact with Delta.

Alarm.Name: AL029
Alarm.Title: Gray code error
Alarm.Result1: The internal address of the encoder is in error.
Alarm.Solve1: Re-power on to operate the motor and check if the alarm will occur again.

Alarm.Name: AL030
Alarm.Title: Motor Crash Error
Alarm.Result1: 1. If it is enabled by mistake, please set P1-57 to zero. 2. According to the actual torque setting, if the value is set too small, the alarm will be triggered by mistake. However, if the value is set too big, it will lose the function of protection.

Alarm.Name: AL031
Alarm.Title: Incorrect wiring of the motor power line U, V, W, GND
Alarm.Result1: The wiring of U, V, W, GND of the motor is incorrect connected.
Alarm.Solve1: Follow the user manual to correctly wire U, V, W and make sure it is grounded.

Alarm.Name: AL040
Alarm.Title: Excessive deviation of full closed-loop position control
Alarm.Result1: Excessive deviation of full closed-loop position control
Alarm.Solve1: 1. Check if P1-73 is set too small. 2. Check if the connector is loose or there is any connection problem of other mechanism.

Alarm.Name: AL041
Alarm.Title: Communication of linear scale is breakdown
Alarm.Result1: The communication of linear scale is breakdown
Alarm.Solve1: Check the communication of linear scale. Check the communication of linear scale again.

Alarm.Name: AL044
Alarm.Title: Warning of Servo Drive function overload
Alarm.Result1: Warning of Servo Drive function overload
Alarm.Solve1: Set P2-66 Bit 4 to 1 can disable the display of this alarm.

Alarm.Name: AL060
Alarm.Title: The absolute position is lost
Alarm.Result1: Battery undervoltage
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the voltage of battery is lower than 2.8V. After changing the battery, conduct homing procedure again.
Alarm.Result2: Change the battery when the power is OFF which is controlled by the servo drive.
Alarm.Solve2: Do not change or remove the battery power when the power is OFF which is controlled by the servo drive. Conduct homing procedure again.
Alarm.Result3: After activating the absolute function, the absolute coordinate initialization has not been completed.
Alarm.Solve3: 1.Install the battery. 2.Check the wiring between the battery pack and power cable of the servo drive. 3. Check the wiring of the encoder. Conduct homing procedure again.
Alarm.Result4: Bad connection of the battery power circuit.
Alarm.Solve4: 1.Check the wiring of the encoder. 2.Check the wiring between the battery pack and the power cable of the servo drive. Connect or repair the wiring of the battery so as to supply the power to the encoder. Conduct homing procedure again.

Alarm.Name: AL061
Alarm.Title: Encoder under voltage
Alarm.Result1: The voltage of the absolute encoder is lower than the specification.
Alarm.Solve1: 1.Check if the voltage of the battery on the panel is lower than 3.1 V( tentative specification) 2.Check if the voltage of the battery is lower than 3.1 V( tentative specification) Change the battery when power is ON which is controlled by the servo drive. After changing the battery, AL061 will be cleared automatically.

Alarm.Name: AL062
Alarm.Title: The multi-turn of absolute encoder overflows
Alarm.Result1: The multi-turn of absolute encoder exceeds the maximum range: -32768 ~+32767
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the operation distance exceeds the range,-32768 ~ +32767, the absolute encoder is able to record. Conduct homing procedure again. Please refer to the description of absolute coordinate initialization in Chapter 12.

Alarm.Name: AL067
Alarm.Title: Encoder temperature warning
Alarm.Result1: Encoder temperature exceeds the warning level.(85~100℃)
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the ventilation devices are normal. Lower the temperature of the encoder.

Alarm.Name: AL069
Alarm.Title: Wrong motor type
Alarm.Result1: Incremental motor is not allowed to activate the absolute function.
Alarm.Solve1: If users desire to use absolute function, please choose absolute motor. If not, please set parameter P2-69 to 0.

Alarm.Name: AL070
Alarm.Title: Encoder does not complete the command which is issued by servo drive
Alarm.Result1: Servo drive has not completely written barcode into encoder or the encoder does not complete the command issued by servo drive.
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the wiring is correct or there is any loose connection.

Alarm.Name: AL072
Alarm.Title: Encoder over speed
Alarm.Result1: When driver provide power,revolution speed will exceed 8800 rpm.When battery provide power,revolution speed will exceed 10000 rpm.
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the servo is properly grounded.Please connect the UVW connector (color green) to the heat sink of the servo drive.
Alarm.Solve2: Check if the encoder cable separates from the power supply or the high-current circuit to avoid the interference.Please check if the encoder cable separates from the power supply or the high-current circuit.
Alarm.Solve3: Check if the shielding cables are used in the wiring of the encoder.Please use shielding mesh.
Alarm.Solve4: Check the status of using is over specification or not.Please do not exceed the specification
Alarm.Solve5: If the situation is not improving, please send the drive back to the distributors or contact with Delta.

Alarm.Name: AL079
Alarm.Title: Encoder Parameter Setting
Alarm.Result1: To let parameter become effective, MS need to be rebooted after setting parameter into encoder.以利參數生效。
Alarm.Solve1: Re-power on。

Alarm.Name: AL099
Alarm.Title: DSP firmware upgrade
Alarm.Result1: Upgrade DSP firmware
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the firmware is upgraded. Firstly set P2-08 to 30. Then set P2-08 to 28, the alarm will be cleared when re-power on.

Alarm.Name: AL111
Alarm.Title: CANopen SDO receives overflow
Alarm.Result1: SDO Rx Buffer overflow (receives more than two SDOs within 1ms)
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the servo drive receives (sends) more than one SDO within 1ms.

Alarm.Name: AL112
Alarm.Title: CANopen PDO receives overflow
Alarm.Result1: PDO Rx Buffer overflow (receives more than two PDOs of COBID within one millisecond)
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the servo drive receives (sends) more than one PDO of COBID within 1ms.

Alarm.Name: AL185
Alarm.Title: Abnormal DMCNET Bus hardware
Alarm.Result1: 1. Check if the communication cable of DMCNET Bus is good. 2. Check if the communication quality is good. (It is suggested to use common grounding and shielded cable)

Alarm.Name: AL201
Alarm.Title: An error occurs when loading DMCNET data
Alarm.Result1: An error occurs when loading DMCNET data
Alarm.Solve1: If the alarm is cleared when re-servo on, it means the data error occurs instantaneously when accessing in the previous time. If the error still exists after re-servo on, it means the data in EEPROM is damaged. It can set P2-08 to 30, 28, and reboot again.

Alarm.Name: AL235
Alarm.Title: PR command overflows
Alarm.Result1: PR command error
Alarm.Solve1: PR mode continuously operates in one direction and causes feedback register overflows. And the coordinate system cannot reflect the correct position. If issuing the absolute positioning command (except incremental) at this time, the error will occur.

Alarm.Name: AL245
Alarm.Title: PR positioning is over time
Alarm.Result1: PR positioning is over time
Alarm.Solve1: This alarm will not occur at the moment. If it does, please contact the distributors.

Alarm.Name: AL283
Alarm.Title: Forward Software Limit
Alarm.Result1: Forward Software Limit
Alarm.Solve1: Fault Reset

Alarm.Name: AL285
Alarm.Title: Reverse Software Limit
Alarm.Result1: Reverse Software Limit
Alarm.Solve1: Fault Reset

Alarm.Name: AL289
Alarm.Title: Feedback position counter overflows
Alarm.Result1: Feedback position counter overflows
Alarm.Solve1: This alarm will not occur at the moment. If it does, please contact the distributors.

Alarm.Name: AL301
Alarm.Title: CANopen fails to synchronize
Alarm.Result1: CANopen fails to synchronize
Alarm.Solve1: 1. Check if the communication quality of the circuit is bad. 2. Check if the controller sends SYNC signal successfully. 3. Check if the setting of P3-09 is reasonable. (It is better to use the default value)

Alarm.Name: AL302
Alarm.Title: The synchronized signal of CANopen is sent too fast
Alarm.Result1: The synchronized signal of CANopen is sent too fast
Alarm.Solve1: 1. Check if synchronized cycle 0x1006 is the same as the setting of controller. 2. Check if the setting of P3-09 is reasonable. (It is better to use the default value) 3. Check if the order of controller is incorrect.

Alarm.Name: AL303
Alarm.Title: The synchronized signal of CANopen is sent too slow
Alarm.Result1: The synchronized signal of CANopen is sent too slow
Alarm.Solve1: 1. Check if the communication quality of the circuit is bad. 2. Check if synchronized cycle 0x1006 is the same as the setting of controller. 3. Check if the setting of P3-09 is reasonable. (It is better to use the default value) 4. Check if the order of controller is incorrect.

Alarm.Name: AL304
Alarm.Title: CANopen IP command fails
Alarm.Result1: CANopen IP command fails
Alarm.Solve1: The calculating time of IP mode takes too long. Please disable USB monitoring function.

Alarm.Name: AL3CF
Alarm.Title: Emergency Deceleration Stop
Alarm.Result1: Press the system emergency deceleration stop switch
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the TP emergency deceleration stop switch is enabled. Activate emergency deceleration stop
Alarm.Result2: Press the external emergency deceleration stop switch
Alarm.Solve2: Check the circuit emergency deceleration stop whether correct
Alarm.Solve3: Check the function of system DI4 whether abnormal
Alarm.Result4: TP Deadman switch emergency deceleration stop
Alarm.Solve4: Please push Deadman switch at middle of position
Alarm.Solve5: Check the fence or safety device whether enableed
Alarm.Result6: Temperature trip emergency deceleration stop switch
Alarm.Solve6: Check the temperature inside the electric control box is too high or the temperature sensor

Alarm.Name: AL500
Alarm.Title: STO function is activated
Alarm.Result1: STO function is activated
Alarm.Solve1: STO function is artificially startup, make sure to startup reasons.
Alarm.Solve2: Please confirm STO contacts and restart the controller.

Alarm.Name: AL501
Alarm.Title: Signal of STO_A missing or wrong
Alarm.Result1: Signal of STO_A missing or STO_A is no synchronization with STO_B more than one second.
Alarm.Solve1: Please confirm STO_A contacts, then fault Reset.

Alarm.Name: AL502
Alarm.Title: Signal of STO_B missing or wrong
Alarm.Result1: Signal of STO_B missing or STO_A is no synchronization with STO_B more than one second.
Alarm.Solve1: Please confirm STO_B contacts, then fault Reset.

Alarm.Name: AL503
Alarm.Title: STO Error
Alarm.Result1: STO is self-diagnostic error
Alarm.Solve1: Check STO_A and STO_B contacts, then fault Reset.

Alarm.Name: AL555
Alarm.Title: System Failure
Alarm.Result1: DSP processing error
Alarm.Solve1: If AL555 occurs, please do not switch and send the drive back to the distributor or contact with Delta

Alarm.Name: AL801
Alarm.Title: Before the coordinate system moves, all-axis original point return is not carried out</Result1>
Alarm.Result1: Before the coordinate system moves, all-axis original point return is not carried out
Alarm.Solve1: Carry out all-axis original point return

Alarm.Name: AL802
Alarm.Title: Give motion command when the alarm occurs
Alarm.Result1: MS has alarm for deceleration stop, this time gave MS motion command
Alarm.Solve1: Please click reset.

Alarm.Name: AL803
Alarm.Title: Motion command does not support overlay mode
Alarm.Result1: Motion command does not support overlay mode
Alarm.Solve1: Single-point MovP, multi-axis MovP, multi-axis Line: these types of motion commands cannot overlap with each other

Alarm.Name: AL80A
Alarm.Title: Motion command interpretation is not prepared properly, unable to interpret
Alarm.Result1: Motion command interpretation is not prepared properly, unable to interpret
Alarm.Solve1: Check if motion command is correct

Alarm.Name: AL80B
Alarm.Title: Motion command cannot be distinguished
Alarm.Result1: Motion command cannot be distinguished
Alarm.Solve1: 1.Check if the motion command code is given correctly. 2.Check the list for support of motion command on the controller

Alarm.Name: AL80C
Alarm.Title: Interpretation error on buffer for motion command
Alarm.Result1: Interpretation error on buffer for motion command
Alarm.Solve1: Check if motion is filled in the correct cache region (single/multiple axes commands are different)

Alarm.Name: AL811
Alarm.Title: Axis error during execution of motion command on Cartesian space
Alarm.Result1: Axis error during execution of motion command on Cartesian space
Alarm.Solve1: 1.Check if the axis is abnormal. 2.Check if status of the axis is normal

Alarm.Name: AL812
Alarm.Title: Axis error during execution of motion command on joint space
Alarm.Result1: Axis error during execution of motion command on joint space
Alarm.Solve1: 1.Check if the axis is abnormal. 2.Check if status of the axis is normal

Alarm.Name: AL813
Alarm.Title: Axis error during interpretation of motion command
Alarm.Result1: Axis error during interpretation of motion command
Alarm.Solve1: 1.Check if the axis is abnormal. 2.Check if status of the axis is normal

Alarm.Name: AL814
Alarm.Title: Axis error during execution of motion command
Alarm.Result1: Axis error during execution of motion command
Alarm.Solve1: 1.Check if the axis is abnormal. 2.Check if status of the axis is normal

Alarm.Name: AL815
Alarm.Title: Axis Out of software-limit
Alarm.Result1: Axis target position is out of software-limit
Alarm.Solve1: Check the target position of command is in space word or not, and press reset button.

Alarm.Name: AL817
Alarm.Title: Set Compensator Error
Alarm.Result1: Compensator only can be set at Robot Group Servo OFF state
Alarm.Solve1: Please check servo status.

Alarm.Name: AL820
Alarm.Title: Vertical articulated robot MovP error
Alarm.Result1: Vertical articulated robot do not support robot language—MovP when executing in Conveyor Tracking application
Alarm.Solve1: Please click reset.

Alarm.Name: AL821
Alarm.Title: Current posture of the robot arm is inconsistent with the target posture
Alarm.Result1: Current posture of the robot arm is inconsistent with the target posture
Alarm.Solve1: 1.Modify the target position posture, or use another motion command. 2.Use the ignore posture setting

Alarm.Name: AL822
Alarm.Title: Target position of the Line command given exceeds working range
Alarm.Result1: Target position of the Line command given exceeds working range
Alarm.Solve1: Check if target position for the Line command is within working range

Alarm.Name: AL823
Alarm.Title: Target position of the Line command given exceeds working range
Alarm.Result1: Target position of the Line command given exceeds working range
Alarm.Solve1: Check if target position for the Line command is within working range

Alarm.Name: AL824
Alarm.Title: Working range exceeded during motion of the space coordinates system
Alarm.Result1: Working range exceeded during motion of the space coordinates system
Alarm.Solve1: Check if the path is within working range

Alarm.Name: AL825
Alarm.Title: Forward Kinematics calculation error
Alarm.Result1: Forward Kinematics calculation error
Alarm.Solve1: 1.Check if settings for mechanical dimension and software limit are correct. 2.Check if the path is within working range

Alarm.Name: AL826
Alarm.Title: Axis motion is over acceleration
Alarm.Result1: Motion speed or acceleration are set too high, resulting in abnormal motion planning
Alarm.Solve1: After click reset, and reduce the motion speed or acceleration.

Alarm.Name: AL829
Alarm.Title: The coordinates system designated by the motion command does not exist
Alarm.Result1: The coordinates system designated by the motion command does not exist
Alarm.Solve1: 1.Check if the coordinates system designated by the motion command is correct. 2.The coordinates system supports three types: world, tool, and users

Alarm.Name: AL82A
Alarm.Title: Switching error of user’s coordinates system
Alarm.Result1: Switching error of user’s coordinates system
Alarm.Solve1: 1.Check if the group of user’s coordinates system designated by the motion command is correct. 2.Check if the coordinates system is taught correctly

Alarm.Name: AL82B
Alarm.Title: Switching error of the tool coordinates system
Alarm.Result1: Switching error of the tool coordinates system
Alarm.Solve1: 1.Check if the group of working coordinates system designated by the motion command is correct. 2.Check if the coordinates system is taught correctly

Alarm.Name: AL82C
Alarm.Title: Target position given exceeds working range
Alarm.Result1: Target position given exceeds working range
Alarm.Solve1: Press reset button and change target position.

Alarm.Name: AL82D
Alarm.Title: Current position given exceeds working range

Alarm.Name: E1.999
Alarm.Title: SCARA 400 arm length
Alarm.Result1: SCARA 400 arm length is set to GMC default value
Alarm.Solve1: Send to service center.

Alarm.Name: EC001
Alarm.Title: PLC timeout
Alarm.Result1: PLC code is too large, make execution time is too long
Alarm.Solve1: Change to a longer PLC cycle execution.
Alarm.Solve2: Check has closed PLC Debug.
Alarm.Solve3: Send the drive back to the distributors or contact with Delta.

Alarm.Name: EC002
Alarm.Title: Library download fail
Alarm.Result1: Library version doesn't match with firmware version
Alarm.Solve1: Check Controller Parameter P1-01 is 1 or not. If P1-01 is 1, because update firmware make library version doesn't match. Please update matching library and restart controller.

Alarm.Name: EC003
Alarm.Title: PLC Exception
Alarm.Result1: PLC Execution Error
Alarm.Solve1: If this alarm happened, please send the drive back to the distributors or contact with Delta.

Alarm.Name: EC004
Alarm.Title: Motion Modules Failure
Alarm.Result1: Function of motion modules is abnormality
Alarm.Solve1: If this alarm happened, don't make any changes, please send the drive back to the distributors or contact with Delta.

Alarm.Name: EC005
Alarm.Title: Controller Failure
Alarm.Result1: Function of controller is abnormality
Alarm.Solve1: If this alarm happened, don't make any changes, please send the drive back to the distributors or contact with Delta.

Alarm.Name: EC006
Alarm.Title: 30 seconds sustained write
Alarm.Result1: 30 seconds sustained write operation
Alarm.Solve1: Check PLC and RL code, or sequential write is caused by operating logic of modbus is incorrect, then Fault Reset.
Alarm.Solve2: If the repeated occurrence. We recommend removal of all external devices to restore the original PLC setting, then debugging step by step.

Alarm.Name: EC007
Alarm.Title: Device settings of DMCNET do not match
Alarm.Result1: Boot-time scan results of DMCNET do not match with parameter setting of power off retentive
Alarm.Solve1: Please check device connection status of DMCNET. Confirm the parameters setting of controller between P3-31 to P3-42 are match with current DMCNET external devices.
Alarm.Solve2: Fault Reset, If you want to change the settings, please re-scanned and stored in parameter setting of power off retentive.

Alarm.Name: EC008
Alarm.Title: Load arm parameter file fail
Alarm.Result1: File format of arm parameter is wrong or file is damaged
Alarm.Solve1: 1.Do not servo on, then restart controller after power off ten minute. 2.If this alarm happened again, don't make any changes, please send the drive back to the distributors.

Alarm.Name: EC009
Alarm.Title: RobotType is Inconsistent
Alarm.Result1: RobotType of parameters setting is inconsistent with currently motion module
Alarm.Solve1: Confirm the firmware version, whether firmware update(down version or failed) caused parameters P1-00 and P0-03 are Inconsistent.
Alarm.Solve2: Reset the parameters P1-00, confirm the current firmware version support this RobotType, the alarm will be cleared when re-power on.

Alarm.Name: EC010
Alarm.Title: Alarm Reset is too often
Alarm.Result1: Alarm Reset be triggered too much, about 1 second 5 times
Alarm.Solve1: Restart controller after power off, do not trigger Alarm Reset too often.

Alarm.Name: EC011
Alarm.Title: PLC Image's variable address has alignment problem
Alarm.Result1: The declared variables is misaligned with PLC Image's variable address
Alarm.Solve1: Check the specified address of declared variable in PLC program witch Type and Address are match or not. For example: Type is DWORD, but address is declared by dividing the remainder by 2 to 4.
Alarm.Solve2: Replace the modified PLC Image and restart controller after power off.

Alarm.Name: EC014
Alarm.Title: Bootloader need to be changed
Alarm.Result1: Bootloader from NAND Flash is crashed
Alarm.Solve1: Please use backup robot then contact OEM to change Bootloader
Alarm.Solve2: Press Alarm Reset.

Alarm.Name: EC015
Alarm.Title: Verification code from NAND Flash is wrong
Alarm.Result1: Nand Flash has numerous invalid Verification code
Alarm.Solve1: Please clean up NAND Flash as soon as posible, and do not power off during the operation.
Alarm.Solve2: Press Alarm Reset.

Alarm.Name: WA001
Alarm.Title: Gating are triggered
Alarm.Result1: Gating are opened or triggered
Alarm.Solve1: Please close the gating and press the reset switch (System DI3) to disarm.

Alarm.Name: WA002
Alarm.Title: Motor temperature is overheat
Alarm.Result1: Motor temperature is overheat
Alarm.Solve1: Stop motion operation temporarily, waiting for motor temperature decreases.

Alarm.Name: WA991
Alarm.Title: Encoder's match code is invalid
Alarm.Result1: Robot does not match with MS
Alarm.Solve1: Please change MS witch match with robot.
